  "chapter": {
    "number": 53,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Suffering Servant"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has believed our message?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And to whom has the arm of the LORD been revealed?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2697
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He grew up before Him like a tender shoot,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and like a root out of dry ground.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He had no stately form or majesty to attract us,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no beauty that we should desire Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He was despised and rejected by men,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a man of sorrows, acquainted with grief.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Like one from whom men hide their faces,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He was despised, and we esteemed Him not.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely He took on our infirmities",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and carried our sorrows;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2698
          },
          {
            "text": "yet we considered Him stricken by God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "struck down and afflicted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But He was pierced for our transgressions,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He was crushed for our iniquities;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the punishment that brought us peace was upon Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and by His stripes we are healed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2699
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We all like sheep have gone astray,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2700
          },
          {
            "text": "each one has turned to his own way;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the LORD has laid upon Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the iniquity of us all.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He was oppressed and afflicted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet He did not open His mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He was led like a lamb to the slaughter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and as a sheep before her shearers is silent,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so He did not open His mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By oppression and judgment He was taken away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and who can recount His descendants?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For He was cut off from the land of the living;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2701
          },
          {
            "text": "He was stricken for the transgression of My people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Grave Assigned"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He was assigned a grave with the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and with a rich man in His death,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "although He had done no violence,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor was any deceit in His mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2702
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet it was the LORD’s will to crush Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to cause Him to suffer;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and when His soul is made a guilt offering,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2703
          },
          {
            "text": "He will see His offspring, He will prolong His days,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the good pleasure of the LORD will prosper in His hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "After the anguish of His soul,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will see the light of life",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2704
          },
          {
            "text": "and be satisfied.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "By His knowledge My righteous Servant will justify many,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will bear their iniquities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will allot Him a portion with the great,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2705
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will divide the spoils with the strong,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2706
          },
          {
            "text": "because He has poured out His life unto death,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He was numbered with the transgressors.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2707
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet He bore the sin of many",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and made intercession for the transgressors.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
